Durban - The driver of a motor vehicle died after allegedly losing control of the car and colliding into a bridge on the N2 near the Tugela, north of Durban on Friday. The car burst into flames on impact said Paul Herbst a spokesperson for IPSS Medical Rescue paramedics. Herbst said the driver had become trapped in the car when it caught alight. Police have to still establish the identity of the driver and cause of the collision. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
